<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 6:17PM MDT  by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Prowers
County through 700 PM MDT...
At 616 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Granada, or 11 miles east of Lamar, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Holly, Granada, Hartman and Bristol.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
